#31500
the Pine Forest~
   The main artery to the northern civilization is to the east.  Looking north
or south will train your eyes just inside the tree line on the shoulder of the
road.  The ground is moist, thick with pine straw and moss.  The soil is rich,
so the trees grow very tall here, the firs of various species are healthy and
quite full.  To the west the forest gets a bit darker as the towering trees
block a great portion of natural light.  The air is clean smells fresh of the
pine sap and campfire.  
~
